The paper deals with domain adaptation in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of distance-based measures and machine learning models also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of sentiment analysis datasets and the mention of image classification in the abstract suggest a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the mention of sample estimates and empirical results suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
